1. Public standard grant

The public Agenticracy standard materials in this repository are made available for academic review, interoperability, non-commercial implementation, reproducibility, and voluntary adoption.

You may:
- read, cite, and discuss the public standard;
- implement the public JSON Schema and public baseline formula for research or non-commercial interoperability;
- create conformant records that disclose public S/P/O/N constructs, G_public, state classes, action classes, and cost-quality telemetry;
- reference the standard with attribution to Vladut-Mihai Iorga and Agenticracy™.

2. Attribution requirement

Any implementation, derivative analysis, paper, dataset, software package, or public claim using this standard must cite:

Vladut-Mihai Iorga, Agenticracy™ Metric public standard, 2026. ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8705-1326.

3. Commercial reservation

Commercial use, paid products, certification, scoring-as-a-service, compliance services, consulting products, model-evaluation products, enterprise integrations, or monetised derivative systems require prior written permission or a commercial licence from psylligent ltd / Workability.ai.

4. Protected implementation layer

This public repository does not license, disclose, or grant rights to:
- AgenticracyXQ™;
- private high-resolution scoring algorithms;
- proprietary synthesis coefficients;
- calibration schedules;
- corrective-pressure or trajectory computations;
- private sycophancy / halo dictionaries;
- verdict thresholds;
- commercial skill implementations or paid metacognition layers.

These remain trade secrets and reserved intellectual property of Vladut-Mihai Iorga / psylligent ltd.

5. Anti-reverse-engineering condition

The public standard is provided to support transparency and interoperability, not to enable adversarial gaming. You may not use public materials, datasets, prompts, or examples to reverse-engineer private scoring weights, private thresholds, protected implementation logic, or commercial AgenticracyXQ™ behaviour.

6. No certification grant

Voluntary conformance with the public standard does not constitute certification, endorsement, warranty, or quality approval. Any commercial certification, audit, or verified scoring programme is separate and may only be offered through authorised commercial vehicles, including Workability.ai where applicable.

7. No warranty

The standard is provided “as is”, without warranty. It is a research and interoperability artefact, not legal, financial, medical, or regulatory advice.
